*   ## **_MJF DEF HECHICERO_**
    

Decent match that ends when MJF hits Hechicero with a Panama Sunrise and a Sheerdrop Brainbuster.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/529e2ad3-5482-4403-91b2-1cd58fbfaec6/20240630_173945.jpg)

*   ## **_THE ELITE DEF SCISSOR ACE(HIROSHI TANAHASHI, THE ACCLAIMED)_**
    

Pretty fun match that existed purely to give AEW fans an Okada/Tanahashi stare down and finishing stretch.

Okada pinned Tanahashi with a Rainmaker.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/fa056d24-f6d5-4c2a-9d56-d3aa01b6f4c2/20240630_180515.jpg)

*   ## **_OWEN HART CUP: BRYAN DANIELSON DEF. SHINGO TAKAGI_**
    

Excellent professional wrestling match. No surprise there. A story about Bryan fighting through a battered body was told here.

Bryan fights his way to a referee's decision over Shingo.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/3a6211e5-6f51-469e-8c17-9ba56684b304/20240630_182657.jpg)

*   ## **_TONI STORM DEF MINA SHIRAKAWA TO RETAIN THE AEW WOMEN'S WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP_**
    

This was legit one of the most over angles of the card and it delivered in the match

Afterwards. Mariah May gets the girls to shake hands and share a 3 way kiss!!!

Happy Pride Month everyone!!!

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/c6151fcf-2de0-464e-ba51-b4d527d594dc/20240630_184833.jpg)

*   ## **_ZACK SABRE JR DEF. ORANGE CASSIDY_**
    

Orange Cassidy came to show off his technical skills against the world's greatest technical wrestler.

And so he did.

But ZSJ has an answer for all of it. In the end, OC was turned into a pretzel and submitted.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/60149bbc-1f42-4876-8dc4-54beb7202964/20240630_190532.jpg)

Katsuyori Shibata, Samoa Joe & HOOK DEF. NJPW Television Champion Jeff Cobb & The Learning Tree (Chris Jericho & Big Bill) (w/ Bryan Keith)

HOOK hits Jericho with his own Judas Effect and it looks better than Jericho's ever did.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d98105d7-d2cf-4f00-85ff-51dc272c3e95/20240630_193008.jpg)

*   ## **JACK PERRY DEF. KONOSUKE TAKESHITA, EL PHANTASMO, MARK BRISCOE, DANTE MARTIN AND LIO RUSH TO BECOME TNT CHAMPION**
    

Great ladder match with a ton of insane spots. Jack Perry takes out Mark Briscoe to grab the belt for himself.

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/10ff62e8-3e1c-4ce6-b936-4697944b4f17/20240630_193451.jpg)

*   ## **_TBS CHAMPIONSHIP AND NJPW STRONG CHAMPIONSHIP: MERCEDES MONE DEF. STEPHANIE VAQUER_**
    

Great match capped off by the return of BRITT BAKER!!!!!

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/71eea899-25bb-451f-890f-018feab16ece/Screenshot_20240630_195800.jpg)

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/a1c143cc-782a-4f37-949b-d81623bfdf7f/Messenger_creation_80bd4884-4eca-489e-9008-6db7406ad7b8.jpeg)

The Forbidden Door concept has reached its final form.

AEW, NJPW, Ring of Honor, STARDOM and CMLL COMING TO THE TOKYO DOME ON JANUARY 5TH, 2025

This was unthinkable just 5 years ago.

Incredible moment in pro wrestling history here.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/acd2e796-9d15-441a-a441-d7aa4986c009/20240630_202225.jpg)

*   ## **_IWGP HEAVYWEIGHT CHAMPIONSHIP: TETSUYA NAITO DEF. JON MOXLEY(c)_**
    

Not the best match. Naito seemed unable to hit the Destino in the closing stretch of the match. Slow moving and the crowd was asleep.

New Champ.

* * *

![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/bcf5c8c5-66bf-4cee-8bd5-152d98179626/20240630_210205.jpg)

*   ## **_AEW WORLD CHAMPIONSHIP: SWERVE STRICKLAND(c) DEF. WILL OSPREAY_**
    

Incredible back and forth match. Don Callis tried to get Will Ospreay to use a screwdriver while the ref was unconscious

Ospreay refused. He kicked out of EVERYTHING Swerve had.

But it was too much. He could not muster enough strength to do anything but reject fate. Swerve Strickland was forced to put Ospreay down for good.

The competitors embrace as Swerve leaves Ospreay with some words and the show closes.